Table 19. Percent of Persons in Poverty, by State: 2016, 2017, and 2018
NOTE: Numbers in thousands. People as of March of the following year.
* Statistically different from zero at the 90 percent confidence level.
(Z) - indicates that the value either represents or rounds to zero.

Standard errors shown in this table are based on standard errors calculated using replicate weights instead of the generalized variance function used in the past. For more information, see Standard Errors and Their Use at <www2.census.gov/library/publications/2019/demo/p60-266sa.pdf>.
For information on confidentiality protection, sampling error, nonsampling error, and definitions, see <www2.census.gov/programs-surveys/cps/techdocs/cpsmar19.pdf>.
